Source: NZ Farmers' Veterinary Guide
Author: EDGAR
Vol / Page: 148
Edition:
Quote: Southland pneumonia: Southland pneumonia is so named because of its occurrence mainly in Otago and Southland and is of unknown origin. It affects early adult ewes, and the incidence is highest while they are suckling their lambs.
